<div id="review_1169071612" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1169071612" />
    <a title="Ryan Lieske" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5889533-ryan-lieske"><img alt="Ryan Lieske" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1517774269p2/5889533.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1169071612?book_show_action=true">Jan 15, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ryan Lieske" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ryan Lieske" href="/user/show/5889533-ryan-lieske">Ryan Lieske</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780451112606" href="/book/show/1649312.Brain">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5889533-ryan-lieske?shelf=mystery-thrillers">mystery-thrillers</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5889533-ryan-lieske?shelf=horror">horror</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1169071612" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13540267550814986222">Ridiculous and fun. I wish all of Cook&apos;s novels were this whacked out and macabre. It&apos;s no &quot;Coma&quot;, but it has the same outlandish thrills as &quot;Mindbend&quot; and &quot;Shock&quot;, which is fine by me. I don&apos;t expect great literature from Dr. Cook; hell, I don&apos;t even expect great storytelling. But &quot;Brain&quot; has just the right amount of B-movie silliness to keep the pages turning. And, since the book was released in the early 80s, a lot of it is hilariously outdated (which, obviously, adds to the fun).</span>
  <span id="freeText13540267550814986222" style="display:none">Ridiculous and fun. I wish all of Cook's novels were this whacked out and macabre. It's no "Coma", but it has the same outlandish thrills as "Mindbend" and "Shock", which is fine by me. I don't expect great literature from Dr. Cook; hell, I don't even expect great storytelling. But "Brain" has just the right amount of B-movie silliness to keep the pages turning. And, since the book was released in the early 80s, a lot of it is hilariously outdated (which, obviously, adds to the fun).</span>
  <a data-text-id="13540267550814986222" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
