<span id="freeTextContainer1191821371870676735">This novel is Dr. Cook&apos;s 4th published novel (Year of the Intern, Coma &amp; Sphinx) and his 2nd medical thriller. It came out 4 years after Coma. It is a mixture of Quincy, ME; Medical Center; Emergency! &amp; Trapper John, MD with a little St. Elsewhere and ER thrown in.<br/><br/>The interesting medical &amp; victimology aspects are: all female, have abnormal pap smears, develop a form of epilepsy &amp; have an attack post OB/GYN exam. Warning: Chapter 6 is particularly graphic for people with weak stomachs.<br/><br/>Ultimately </span>
  <span id="freeText1191821371870676735" style="display:none">This novel is Dr. Cook's 4th published novel (Year of the Intern, Coma &amp; Sphinx) and his 2nd medical thriller. It came out 4 years after Coma. It is a mixture of Quincy, ME; Medical Center; Emergency! &amp; Trapper John, MD with a little St. Elsewhere and ER thrown in.<br /><br />The interesting medical &amp; victimology aspects are: all female, have abnormal pap smears, develop a form of epilepsy &amp; have an attack post OB/GYN exam. Warning: Chapter 6 is particularly graphic for people with weak stomachs.<br /><br />Ultimately this novel along with his previous work Coma shows the danger of lax medical research ethics and the inherent dangers of socialized medicine.</span>
