<div id="review_2455984065" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2455984065" />
    <a title="Carol Lynn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11791638-carol-lynn"><img alt="Carol Lynn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1344782240p2/11791638.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2455984065?book_show_action=true">Jul 15, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Carol Lynn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Carol Lynn" href="/user/show/11791638-carol-lynn">Carol Lynn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/6626184-brain">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2455984065" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10261949695565097217"><strong>Hair-raising medical intrigue</strong><br/><br/>How to fit the puzzle pieces together? Another of Robin&apos;s excellent &quot;medical thrillers&quot; ... until close to the end . Then it got scary. And scarier. <br/>Don&apos;t stop reading at the end. The epilogue will ruin your night&apos;s sleep. <br/>I&apos;m off to start a bit of &quot;horse fluff&quot; so I can sleep in a little while.<br/>Thanks, Robin, for giving me the willies.</span>
  <span id="freeText10261949695565097217" style="display:none"><strong>Hair-raising medical intrigue</strong><br /><br />How to fit the puzzle pieces together? Another of Robin's excellent "medical thrillers" ... until close to the end . Then it got scary. And scarier. <br />Don't stop reading at the end. The epilogue will ruin your night's sleep. <br />I'm off to start a bit of "horse fluff" so I can sleep in a little while.<br />Thanks, Robin, for giving me the willies.</span>
